    <body>
      <section eId="sec_2998_F">
        <num>2998-F</num>
        <heading>Reporting of the health risk factors of excessive alcohol consumption</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_2998_F__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>information on excessive alcohol consumption and alcohol poisoning\ndeaths, including age, gender, ethnicity, and geographic location;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2998_F__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>data on emergency room utilization for the treatment of alcohol\npoisoning; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2998_F__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>any other information necessary to ascertain areas of the state\nwhich are experiencing particularly high rates of excessive alcohol\nconsumption and alcohol poisoning, ways to determine if services,\nresources, and responses in particular areas of the state area having a\npositive impact on reducing excessive alcohol consumption and alcohol\npoisoning. Such reporting may be through a web-based dashboard.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
